  "name": "Romans 4:1–25",
  "localizedName": "Romans 4:1–25",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Jews knew that God had made a "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108253",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "covenant with Abraham"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". God had promised him land to live on and a very big family."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108243",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Abraham"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " hadn’t done anything to deserve this promise. Abraham and "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108247",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Sarah"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " were too old to have children. Even so, Abraham believed that God would keep his promise."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "He had hope in God and faith that God could do anything he wanted to. God was very pleased that Abraham believed him. God made Abraham right with himself."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Being made right with God is a blessing. This blessing is for everyone who has faith like Abraham had. People who have faith like Abraham’s faith are also Abraham’s children. They are his children even if they aren’t from his family line."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Paul explained how Abraham’s faith is connected to Jesus. The God that Abraham believed in is the God who raised Jesus from the dead. Everyone who "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108255",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "believes in"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Jesus is made right with God."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
